cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a new normalization technique for neural networks and evaluates its performance on various datasets using fully-connected and convolutional networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the impact of the proposed technique on internal covariate shift, which suggests a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
